programme.title: Dealers Put Your Money Where Your Mouth Is
programme.desc: Some people play the lottery, others dream of unearthing a valuable antique treasure at Saturday morning garage sales. Your odds of achieving the latter may improve drastically thanks to this series that asks expert antiques dealers to reveal their secrets of turning trash to treasure as they are challenged to put their money where their mouth is. At the end of their shopping spree, their loot is sent to auction. The dealer who walks away with the most profit reigns supreme.

programme.title: Mudcats
programme.desc: Along Oklahoma's many rivers, a group of daring men practise a tradition dating back to early pioneer days, catching giant catfish with nothing more than their bare hands. Catfish "noodling"is a way to supplement incomes during the regulated catfish season. The colourful characters who practice it brave snakes, bugs, riptides, and more, reaching into muddy waters, using their fingers as bait for giant fish that weigh up to 30 pounds. This series will celebrate this uniquely all-American tradition while showing the little-known world of Mudcatters.

programme.title: Big Shrimpin'
programme.desc: Follow the adventures, trials and tribulations of Dominic "The Dom", owner of a fleet of six shrimp boats in the Gulf of Mexico, and his crew of shrimpers from Alabama. They have 30 days across June and July to make their money by scouring the Gulf, looking for the best territory to drag their heavy funnel-shaped trawl nets over the sea floor like a mule pulling a plow. Shrimping has been part of the Gulf since the 17th century when fisherman used vertical nets up to 600 feet in diameter to scoop up the delicacy. With the invention of the flat bottom "otter trawl"along with motorised engines, the territory and depth of shrimping expanded. Currently the US harvests over half million pounds of shrimp and imports another 200 million pounds a year, more than any other country. The competition is fierce among Dom's boats, each crew working hard to bring in the biggest haul for the biggest payday. Travel with the Shrimpers as they battle each other, the weather and crew from other companies.

programme.title: Who's Been Sleeping In My House
programme.desc: About 500 kms east of Perth, on the fringe of the Western Desert, sits the outback town of Coolgardie. In the 1890s it exploded into life with the discovery of gold, and became a ghost town almost overnight when the gold dried up. Today only a few of the grand buildings from Coolgardie's heyday survive, and one of them is Peter Pan. Tex and Margaret Moore have a remarkable history with Peter Pan that makes their bond with it particularly strong. They first laid eyes on it in the 1970s when the house was in ruins, but it was love at first sight. They began rebuilding it, a monumental task that took eight years. But what makes Tex and Margaret's renovation story so different is they didn't even own the house. It was in the hands of the Public Trustee, and for years they slaved away at restoring Peter Pan in the hope that one day they could buy it. Eventually they did. Coolgardie's a tough old mining town. A fairytale name is the last thing you'd expect out here. So who named it Peter Pan, and why? Also, despite the house being in ruins, the couple has always wondered about the only furniture to survive the years of ransacking - a set of dining chairs with sinister, demonic heads carved onto their backs. And finally, there's a local legend that a barman once hid in Peter Pan's cellar whilst trying to escape an angry lynch mob from nearby Kalgoorlie. Could it be true?

programme.desc: A thrilling investigative drama exploring the personal and professional lives of two female detectives. Detective Constable Rachel Bailey is 30, down-to-earth, noisy, argumentative and single. She's a hardworking, committed detective. She had been in a relationship with a barrister, Nick, until he left her for the wife she didn't know he had. Meanwhile her colleague, Detective Constable Janet Scott is 40, a diplomat and a thinker, as well as being a wife and mother to two teenage girls. She had very strong reasons for wanting to be a detective - her friend was murdered when they were children and the crime has never been solved. They both work for Manchester Metropolitan Police's prestigious Murder Investigation Team and, despite the obvious differences between them, they have developed a robust friendship. Co-created by award-winning writer Sally Wainwright and ex-Detective Inspector Diane Taylor, formerly of the Major Incident Team at Greater Manchester Police, Scott And Bailey is an honest, powerful and funny crime drama series. In this opening episode, angry at being dumped by married lover Nick, Manchester detective Rachel Bailey joins married colleague Janet Scott to investigate the murder, made to resemble a suicide, of Emel Yilmatz, a pregnant teen age Turkish girl. And Janet is approached by old friend Geoff to reopen a dead case.

In the Night Garden is a thoroughly modern interpretation of a nursery rhyme picture book, and takes children on an imaginative journey to meet a host of wonderfully silly characters living together within a happy and caring community. programme.desc: In the rugged mountains of British Columbia in Canada, there's a highway like no other. An unforgiving, white-knuckle ride that thousands of truckers must run every day. Keeping the Coquihalla Highway open takes an army of men and machines and the last line of defense is the fleet of Jamie Davis Heavy Rescue. Jamie's team is willing to tackle any disaster the mountain throws at them. They have been entrusted to keep some of the most economically important and inhospitable roads in Canada open and safe during the winter season. The stakes are high - lives, the economy and thousands of jobs depend on the highways staying clear, but the extreme mountain roads are fraught with steep, icy terrain where Mother Nature reigns supreme. During winter storms truckers crash and close the road every twelve hours on average and when they do, the call goes out to the team of heavy rescue tow truck drivers who are on call 24/7. Even the toughest men in the towing business are pushed to breaking point; they have witnessed some horrific scenes. The drivers must brave the extreme temperatures and seemingly impossible conditions to remove often dangerous cargo, clean up the carnage and get the truck traffic rolling again. Fast.

programme.sub-title: I Spy With My Little Eyes
programme.desc: Follow the adventures of seven-year-old Charlie and his feisty little sister Lola in this fresh, exuberant, delightfully witty animation based on the award-winning picture books by Lauren Child. Charlie is seven. He is loving, patient, and very bright. His little sister Lola is four going on five. She is small, mischievous and very funny. Together they deal with the numerous dilemmas that every small child encounters - dealing with your first wobbly tooth, staying neat and tidy for your first school photograph, not particularly liking spiders or simply just wishing you were bigger. These little stumbling blocks spiral into a succession of imaginative games, role-play and flights of fancy (normally invented by Charlie) to coax his spirited little sister Lola round to seeing things in a more reasoned way. Eating yucky, sticky mashed potato instantly becomes an expedition to the top of Mount Fuji tasting spoonfuls of cloud fluff. Going to bed is much more fun if it involves drinking pink milk with tigers and shooing whales down the plughole. And tomatoes? Well, they're not really tomatoes. They're Moonsquirters from the land of Moon! Charlie and Lola series two consists of 26x12 minute episodes screening weekdays at 4.05pm from Friday, April 27 on ABC Kids.

programme.title: In The Night Garden
programme.sub-title: Where Did Makka Pakka's Sponge Go?
programme.desc: In the Night Garden is about a magical picture-book place that exists between waking and sleeping in a child's imagination. Reached by following a magical little blue star, the Night Garden is a warm and affectionate world which is home to a comical and diverse community of toys, living happily together, and who care for each other unconditionally. In the Night Garden is a thoroughly modern interpretation of a nursery rhyme picture book, and takes children on an imaginative journey to meet a host of wonderfully silly characters living together within a happy and caring community. It is both funny and reassuring, with a capacity to relax and entertain. The tone of the program is deliberately literary. Words, rhymes and music carry the viewer through a happy world of loveable characters and nursery rhyme nonsense. Filmed in real woodland, the setting is breathtaking and the program weaves together the very latest technical innovations in live-character costume technology and computer animation, to create a compelling and fully immersing experience for young viewers.

programme.title: The Mysterious Cities Of Gold
programme.desc: The year is 1532. Esteban, a young boy, is told that he was saved by Mendoza, a navigator on a Spanish ship from a ship wreck in a storm at sea. The only clue to his identity is a medal that Esteban wears about his neck. Esteban joins Mendoza on a trip from Spain to the new world - the Americas - where on route he meets two other children - Zia - an Inca girl and Tao, the last member of a highly advanced race. All three are looking for different things - Esteban to find his father and his identity, Zia for her father and Tao for remains of his race. The clues for all three quests however all point to the seven Cities of Gold and so the children, Mendoza, Sancho and Pedro - two other sailors and friends of Mendoza start searching in a massive treasure hunt for the Cities Of Gold...

programme.title: Owl's Odyssey
programme.desc: When a female barn-owl's home - an old disused barn - is demolished, she has to seek a new place to live. On the way, flying through forests and across grasslands, she encounters most of the common owl species in Central Europe: long - and short-eared owls, little, tawny and eagle owls, some she can live peacefully beside, others she must shun or risk becoming their prey. During her journey, the film shows how owls fly so silently and hunt so efficiently; it illustrates what they have meant to humans since ancient times, and how they live beside us today. It explains why they have become - unfairly - associated with death. Our owl finally finds a new home, as the guest of a barn owl family, in time to see the new clutch of young following their mother on their first majestic flight. (From Austria, in English) G CC

programme.title: Owl's Odyssey
programme.desc: When a female barn-owl's home - an old disused barn - is demolished, she has to seek a new place to live. On the way, flying through forests and across grasslands, she encounters most of the common owl species in Central Europe: long - and short-eared owls, little, tawny and eagle owls, some she can live peacefully beside, others she must shun or risk becoming their prey. During her journey, the film shows how owls fly so silently and hunt so efficiently; it illustrates what they have meant to humans since ancient times, and how they live beside us today. It explains why they have become - unfairly - associated with death. Our owl finally finds a new home, as the guest of a barn owl family, in time to see the new clutch of young following their mother on their first majestic flight. (From Austria, in English) G CC

programme.title: Ching's Restaurant Redemption
programme.desc: Ching-He Huang's next restaurant seems like a lost cause from the get go. Hidden in a nondescript mall in Pennsylvania with no obvious signage, it's a challenge to find it. Frank and Vivian Dominick gave up their careers to run Fusion Fire with no prior restaurant experience. The original concept was Chinese hot pot, but that proved unpopular with locals during the hot Pennsylvanian summers. To add to their difficulties, several years ago Frank's head sushi chef and three other staff quit. With every penny they own invested in the business, Frank and Vivian refused to give up. This loving couple lost their head chef and now they've lost their way. Can Ching give them the direction they need before they lose their livelihood?

programme.title: Bronson
programme.desc: "In introducing himself, Michael "Charles Bronson" Peterson (Tom Hardy) tells his audience that he sought fame from an early age, but did not have conventional talents. It is soon apparent that his talent lies in other areas, as he takes on a number of prison guards in a cage fight. Peterson's early life is shown in flashback, as his violent tendencies begin to surface at school. At the age of 19, his robbery of a post office sends him to prison for seven years, where he comes into his psychopathic element. Creating constant havoc by starting fights with prison officers sees Peterson shunted around various prisons and eventually a psychiatric hospital. He is eventually paroled, and starts boxing, taking on the stage name of Charles Bronson. Inevitably, Bronson ends up back in prison, and notches up 30 years in solitary confinement, which only heightens his distorted and evil take on reality, and ensures his infamy instead of fame."

programme.desc: Forget about homework and pop quizzes. The students of Class 3E have a far more important assignment: kill their teacher before the end of the year! Should some eager beaver prove to be a quick study in killing, he or she will save Earth from extinction - and collect a hefty reward. But they'd better take some serious notes while class is in session because their slaughtering sensei has eight deadly tentacles just waiting to wreak havoc on humanity. programme.title: Star Trek
programme.desc: The greatest adventure of all time begins with a young crew's maiden voyage on board the most advanced starship ever created: the USS Enterprise. In the midst of an incredible journey full of optimism, intrigue, comedy and cosmic peril, the new recruits must find a way to stop an evil being whose mission of vengeance threatens all of mankind. The fate of the galaxy rests in the hands of bitter rivals born worlds apart. James Tiberius Kirk (Chris Pine), a delinquent, thrill-seeking Iowa farm boy, a natural-born leader in search of a cause and Spock (Zachary Quinto), reared on the planet Vulcan, an outcast due to his half-human background, which makes him susceptible to the volatile emotions that Vulcans have long lived without, and yet an ingenious, determined student, who will become the first of his kind accepted into the Starfleet Academy. Kirk and Spock could not be more different. Yet, in their quest to figure out who they really are and what they have to give to the world, they soon become competitive cadets. With their drastically opposite styles, one driven by fiery passion, the other by rigorous logic, they also become defiant, contentious adversaries, each equally unimpressed with the other, each going all out to be among the special few chosen to join the crew of the most advanced starship ever created, the USS Enterprise. The all-star cast includes Eric Bana, Simon Pegg, Winona Ryder, Zoe Saldana, Bruce Greenwood and Leonard Nimoy.
